BY virtue of the King's commission of the peace, oyer and terminer, and goal-delivery of Newgate, holden for the city of London and county of Middlesex, at
Justice-hall in the Old Baily, before the
Right Honourable William Beckford Esq. Lord Mayor ;
Sir Henry Gould, Knt. one of the Judges of his Majesty's court of Common Pleas ;
George Perrott, Esq. one of the Barons of his Majesty's court of Exchequer ;
Sir William Moreton, Knt. Recorder ;
James Eyre, Esq. deputy Recorder , and others of his Majesty's Justices of oyer and terminer of the city of London, and Justices of goal-delivery of Newgate, &c. holden for the said city and county, on Wednesday the 23d, Thursday the 24th, and Friday the 25th of February, in the third year of his Majesty's reign, two persons, viz.
Daniel Blake, and Elizabeth, otherwise
Esther Lyon, were capitally convicted, and received sentence of death, for the several crimes in their indictments.
